  "description": "MetaRDK is a neuroimaging dataset containing intracranial EEG recordings from epileptic patients performing a perceptual decision-making task with confidence judgments. Patients discriminated the direction of random dot motion while their neural activity was recorded, with difficulty titrated to 70% accuracy. The dataset includes high-gamma band activity (70-150 Hz) and behavioral measures, enabling investigation of neural correlates of evidence accumulation, confidence, and changes of mind in decision-making processes.",
  "methods_description": "Intracranial EEG recordings were obtained from pharmacologically intractable epilepsy patients using a Micromed recording system. Patients performed a perceptual decision task requiring discrimination of dot motion direction within 6 seconds, followed by confidence ratings on a 0-100 scale. High-gamma activity was extracted as average power modulation across five non-overlapping frequency bands between 70-150 Hz, sampled at 512 Hz. Data were segmented from trial onset to offset and screened to remove epilepsy-related artifacts.",
